---
title: Meatloaf à la Mom with Roasted Root Veggies and Thyme Gravy
description: It’s commonly agreed that no one makes meatloaf quite like Mom. But our chefs will settle for second best by taking a page from her book and passing on this recipe that stays about as true to tradition as can be. These ground beef mini loaves are brushed with a ketchup glaze, served with tender roasted carrots and potatoes, and drizzled with an herby thyme gravy. And if you’d like to claim this recipe as your own, don’t worry—we’ll stay mum.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5e28600710607e22821be807-c69f865a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/meatloaf-a-la-mom-5e28600710607e22821be807-c0147884.pdf
time required: 45 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/meatloaf-a-la-mom-5e28600710607e22821be807
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 33 g
  sodium: 1200 g
servings: 2
cuisine: American
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve and peel @shallot{1}. Grate one half on the largest holes of a #box grater{}; place in a #medium bowl{} (use a #large bowl{} for 4 servings). Mince remaining shallot. Mince @garlic clove{2}(minced). Strip @thyme{1/4%bunch} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves and discard stems. Halve @baby carrots{8} lengthwise. Cut @russet potatoes{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Toss potato on a separate baking sheet with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast, swapping baking sheet positions halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes} total (we'll add more ingredients to sheet with potato after ~{7%minutes}).

Meanwhile, to #bowl{} with grated shallot, add @ground beef{10%oz}, garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, half the thyme, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and pepper. Gently combine, then form mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4).

Once potato has roasted ~{7%minutes}, remove baking sheet from oven, leaving carrots roasting. Push potato to one side of sheet. Place meatloaves on empty side; brush tops of loaves with half the @ketchup{2%tbsp} (all the ketchup for 4 servings). Return to oven and continue roasting until meatloaves are cooked through and potato is tender, ~{15-18%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1/2%tbsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add minced shallot and remaining thyme. Cook, stirring, until shallot is softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Sprinkle @flour{1%tbsp} into pan; stir vigorously to combine. Whisk in @beef stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/2%cup} (1 cup for 4). Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened and saucy, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice meatloaves crosswise. Divide meatloaves, carrots, and potato between plates. Spoon gravy over meatloaves and serve.